         <abstract>
            <p>This article is an expansion of the notes to a one-hour lecture for an MSRI workshop on computational number theory. The editors of Mathematics of Computation kindly asked us to submit these notes for publication, and we are enormously pleased to do so. Our original audience did not consist of experts in the field of modular forms, and we have tried to keep this article accessible to nonexperts.</p>
          </abstract>
